latestIgtvVideos.caption:
At the start of 2021, we released 
A labor of many years in the making.
A project very close to my heart. 
It was embraced like I would have never imagined. 

Simple videos about Cool The Globe were 
viewed and shared by millions around the globe. 
People from all walks of life got in touch, to contribute, to give suggestions 
and even just to convey words of encouragement. 

It is because of those very voices, that now, we enter a new phase. 
What started in my dorm room of a young media student, 
is turning into a citizen led movement for climate action. 

As Cool The Globe reaches a 11,000 + user base
From over 55 countries, 
Sharing this video here as a reminder,
that when citizens come together, 
Miracles can happen!

In today’s Youth Bite, meet @prachi.shevgaonkar 🇮🇳, an inspiring and passionate youth delegate from India, recognized as the ‘Young Change-maker of the Year’ by the finance minister of India. Gain a glimpse into her journey of launching the app “Cool the Globe,” which she founded back in college, and hear her perspective on youth voices and climate action.

By the way, Prachi is also a member of the @gcarcticangels , the Youth-Led Intergenerational Action Network you’ve already explored in our Arctic Fair Talk series. Stay tuned for another insightful interview with one of their members later this week! 👀

From COP29 in Baku, Azerbaijan, Prachi Shevgaonkar, founder of Cool The Globe , shares a powerful insight: real change isn’t made only in conference rooms; it’s driven by citizens like YOU.

From locals in Baku choosing public transport 🚍 to 100K+ users across 150 countries 🌏 cutting their carbon footprints, Cool The Globe proves that small, consistent actions spark big, systemic changes.

And here’s the dream: a future COP where every delegate walks the talk, leading by example and taking climate action right on the venue.

Stay tuned for more on the groundbreaking solutions shaping our climate future! 🌱✨

latestPosts.caption: Ways to compensate for the height 😭😂

In 2023 I went to @oneyoungworld in Belfast, and shared our mission to Cool The Globe. During my speech, something very interesting happened.

Many delegates used to walk from the hotel to the event venue. Using Cool The Globe App, I shared the emissions we were saving with this simple action.

People loved it!

Hundreds of delegates came to me buzzing with excitement and asked about other climate actions they could take during the event.

That gave root to an idea that has come to life today.

I am excited to share that I came to One Young World as a delegate speaker last year, and this year, we have become their sustainability partners.

One Young World will be using Cool The Globe App to drive climate action at the summit.

On the app, delegates can calculate their event footprint, pledge to reduce it, join our sustainability challenges, compete with fellow delegates, offset their emissions and much more. Cool The Globe will track in real time the collective climate impact of all delegates.

One Young World is just the beginning.

We hope to see every event driving climate action and Cool The Globe is here to help! 🌍

Which event do you think we should take on next? Let me know in the comments :)
